# 📚 NLP Stack Overflow Post Categorization

This project analyzes and categorizes over 20,000 Stack Overflow posts related to Natural Language Processing (NLP), using data collected via the Stack Exchange API.

## 🔍 Project Overview

- Collected NLP-tagged posts from Stack Overflow
- Preprocessed post titles, questions, and accepted answers
- Created word clouds and basic visualizations
- Designed a rule-based multi-label classification system
- Categorized posts into:
  - Implementation Issues
  - Tool Specific
  - NLP Tasks
  - Conceptual Understanding

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python (Pandas, NLTK, spaCy, Matplotlib)
- Stack Exchange API
- Jupyter Notebook

## 📁 Dataset

The full dataset is **not included** due to GitHub file size limits.

> You can reproduce the dataset using the provided code and your own Stack Exchange API key.

## 📎 Files

- `NLP_A2.ipynb` — Main notebook (includes data collection, processing, visualization, classification)
- `figures/` — Word cloud and plots
- `README.md` — Project description

